AWS Console (Step by Step)

Step 1 — Create IAM Role for EKS Cluster

1. Go to IAM → Roles → Create Role
2. Select EKS → EKS Cluster
3. Attach policy: AmazonEKSClusterPolicy
4. Name it: eks-cluster-role


Step 2 — Create IAM Role for Worker Nodes

1. Go to IAM → Roles → Create Role
2. Select EC2
3. Attach these policies:

   • AmazonEKSWorkerNodePolicy
   • AmazonEKS_CNI_Policy
   • AmazonEC2ContainerRegistryReadOnly

4. Name it: eks-node-role

Step 3 — Create VPC & Networking

Or manually create:

• VPC with CIDR 10.0.0.0/16
• 2 Public Subnets
• 2 Private Subnets
• Internet Gateway
• NAT Gateway
• Route Tables


Step 4 — Create EKS Cluster

1. Go to EKS → Clusters → Create Cluster
2. Enter Cluster Name (e.g., my-eks-cluster)
3. Select Kubernetes version (e.g., 1.29)
4. Select Cluster IAM Role → eks-cluster-role
5. Select VPC and Subnets
6. Set Security Groups
7. Set Cluster Endpoint Access:
   
   • Public (default)
   • Private
   • Public & Private

8. Configure Logging (optional)
9. Click Create (takes 10–15 mins)

Step 5 — Add Node Group

1. Go to your cluster → Compute → Add Node Group
2. Enter Node Group Name
3. Select Node IAM Role → eks-node-role
4. Choose AMI type → Amazon Linux 2
5. Set Instance type (e.g., t3.medium)
6. Set Scaling config:

   • Min: 1
   • Max: 4
   • Desired: 2

7. Select Subnets (private subnets recommended)
8. Click Create
